  "prompt": "Do you think the promise made by BJP of giving 15 lakhs to every Indians account will be true?",
  "response": "As an AI, I don't have opinions, but I can provide some analysis based on facts and historical context. The promise made by the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) regarding depositing \u20b915 lakh into every Indian's bank account has been widely discussed and debated. This promise was part of the political rhetoric during the 2014 elections in India, often attributed to Narendra Modi's campaign speeches.\n\nHowever, implementing such a policy would present significant economic and logistical challenges. India has a population of over 1.3 billion people, and depositing \u20b915 lakh into each individual's account would amount to an astronomical sum that the Indian economy currently can't support without severe repercussions such as inflation, economic imbalance, and increased national debt.\n\nMoreover, political promises are often shaped by the context of the campaign and may not be feasible in practical terms. As of now, there is no indication that such a promise has been realistic, practical, or integrated into the government\u2019s fiscal policies. It\u2019s essential to critically evaluate political claims and understand the broader economic implications they might carry.",
